sentences: Adolphus Acquah Robertson Turkson (12 September 1933 – 21 June 1993), better known as Ato Turkson, was a Ghanaian composer and musicologist.
He studied music at the University of Ghana, graduating in 1964.
He was also visiting scholar at the University of Cologne (1978) and Portland State University (1982).

His best-known work is Three pieces for flute and piano (1968).
